This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with human parsing and pose estimation, which are important topics in computer vision. Additionally, the paper proposes a joint human parsing and pose estimation network, which is a common research area in computer vision. 

The paper also involves machine learning techniques, such as deep learning, which suggests that it could belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. 

The paper proposes a new benchmark dataset, which could fall under the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category as it involves creating a comprehensive dataset for future developments in human-centric analysis. 

The dataset contains images with a broad range of viewpoints, occlusions, and background complexities, which suggests that it could belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. 

Finally, the paper proposes a self-supervised structure-sensitive learning approach, which could fall under the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category as it involves exploring novel approaches to solve human parsing without extra supervision.
